summary: This is an email chain from October 2021 regarding a draft FBI 302 document related to a trash pull and records from the Palm Beach Police Department. The email is between law enforcement personnel, including a detective from the NYPD/FBI Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force, concerning case files.

persons.name: Amanda
persons.context: Appears as the sender of an email on October 8, 2021, attaching the PBPD Trash Pull and records, and cautioning about external senders.

events.title: PBPD Trash Pull and Records Received
events.description: An email from 'Amanda' attaches the Palm Beach Police Department Trash Pull along with records received that day.

events.title: Draft 302 Forwarded
events.description: A draft FBI 302 document for case files, picked up on the previous Friday, is forwarded via email.

keyFacts: A draft FBI 302 document related to case files was circulated among law enforcement in October 2021.
The email references a 'PBPD Trash Pull' and associated records, indicating ongoing investigative evidence collection.
The communication involves the NYPD/FBI Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force, highlighting inter-agency cooperation.
The email includes a standard security warning about external senders, typical for official law enforcement correspondence.
